22	// US-040 — Campaign detail screen. Gated under the creator tab group so
23	// the shared TabBar stays visible; route matches the story AC
24	// (`app/(creator)/listing/[id].tsx`). Data flows through the
25	// get-listing-detail edge function (US-039) — that path is picked
26	// deliberately over direct PostgREST so it works around the current
27	// JWT-drift cascade that blocks gateway-verified table reads.
28	//
29	// Spec alignment (docs/design.md §4.2):
30	// - Back chevron header (lister handle deferred — requires a lister-profile
31	//   join the edge function does not yet expose; Spec gap noted in progress.txt).
32	// - Hero card with title, price, "Payout after approval" caption.
33	// - Sample videos rendered as tappable rows that open the URL in the
34	//   platform app via Linking.openURL — NOT embedded previews per the
35	//   design doc's "link-out only" v1 rule.
36	// - Eligibility rail: one row per PRE condition showing ✓/✗ plus the
37	//   required threshold and the creator's actual value (from the
38	//   edge-function `failed_conditions` additive `actual` field).
39	// - "What to film" post-condition bullet list (POST rows; not gated on
40	//   eligibility — reviewed at submission time, US-057+).
41	// - Sticky footer with the Apply CTA. Gate per §4.2:
42	//     eligible + !active-app  → ButtonPrimary "Apply to collab"
43	//     eligible + active-app   → StatusPill + disabled CTA
44	//     ineligible              → disabled CTA "Not eligible yet"
45	//     inactive listing        → no CTA, status banner at top
46	//
47	// Apply flow itself lands in US-041 (server-side re-check edge function)
48	// + US-042 (modal + toast). This screen's CTA currently surfaces a toast
49	// stub so the tap target is exercised during mobile-mcp verification.
